3352	  it suffices to verify that the sheafified presheaf comparison
3353	  \(a_Y.\mathrm{map}\,(\delta\,(\mathtt{pullback}\,\varphi')\,\mathbf{1}\,\mathbf{1})\)
3354	  is an isomorphism; the underlying presheaf of the structure-sheaf unit coincides with
3355	  the presheaf monoidal unit \(\mathbf{1}\).
3356	
3357	  On the unit pair the presheaf-level oplax comparison \(\delta\) is governed by Mathlib's
3358	  oplax-monoidal \emph{unit coherence}: \(\mathtt{Functor.OplaxMonoidal.left\_unitality\_hom}\)
3359	  expresses \(\delta\,(\mathtt{pullback}\,\varphi')\,\mathbf{1}\,\mathbf{1}\) as a composite of
3360	  the functorial unitor \(F.\mathrm{map}\,(\lambda_{\mathbf{1}}).\mathrm{hom}\), the target
3361	  unitor \(\lambda_{F.\mathrm{obj}\,\mathbf{1}}\), and the whiskered presheaf unit comparison
3362	  \(\eta\,(\mathtt{pullback}\,\varphi') \rhd F.\mathrm{obj}\,\mathbf{1}\). The unitors are
3363	  isomorphisms, so after sheafification by \(a_Y\) the genuine remaining content is
3364	  \[
3365	    \mathtt{IsIso}\bigl(a_Y.\mathrm{map}\,(\eta\,(\mathtt{pullback}\,\varphi'))\bigr),
3366	  \]
3367	  the sheafified presheaf unit comparison (the \(\delta\)-wrapping reduction). By \cref{lem:isiso_sheafifyeta_of_unitsquare} it suffices, in turn, to prove the
3368	  \emph{unit square}
3369	  \[
3370	    (\mathtt{pullbackValIso}\,f\,\mathcal{O}_X).\mathrm{inv} \mathbin{;}
3371	      a_Y.\mathrm{map}\,(\eta\,(\mathtt{pullback}\,\varphi')) \mathbin{;}
3372	      \mathtt{sheafifyUnitIso}.\mathrm{hom}
3373	      \;=\; \mathtt{pullbackObjUnitToUnit}\,\varphi,
3374	  \]
